s guaranteed to contain an optimal policy and also, obtain such a policy. Finally, we analyze a generalization in which the principal has a limited number for rewards in any given period and show that the class of score-based policies, with modifications to accommodate the limited availability of the rewards, continues to contain an optimal solution for the principal.This paper was accepted by Jeannette Song, operations management.Supplemental Material: The online appendix is available at https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.2022.4482.
